
INSTALL

You want to install utils-menu? Run the following command and it will
install itself for you (utils-menu will be installed in ~/.utils-menu)

	curl -L http://goo.gl/b2pmx > .utils-menu-install && bash ./.utils-menu-install && rm .utils-menu-install

If you want to install utils-menu in a different directory, it's easy!
For example, to install utils-menu at ~/.utils-menu, just run:

	curl -L http://goo.gl/b2pmx > .utils-menu-install && UTILS_PROJECT_PATH=~/.utils-menu bash ./.utils-menu-install && rm .utils-menu-install
  
For more details about this program, visit http://github.com/regedor/Utils-menu

